Pre-K for All gives every four-year-old in New York City the opportunity to have a strong start in school and life. Pre-K classrooms across New York City are full of joy and discovery as children learn to problem-solve, ask questions, and explore the world around them.3-K for All brings free, full-day, high-quality education to three-year-old children in New York City, in a growing number of communities.

Pre-K and 3-K applications for the 2019-20 school year are no longer available. All families who applied by the application deadline received their results in May.

Didn't submit an application? You can still participate - search for programs and add your child to waitlists today! To add your child to waitlists, visit MySchools.nyc, call 718-935-2009, or visit a Family Welcome Center

To learn more about pre-K, read the 2019-20 Pre-K Admissions Guide.

In fall 2019, 3-K for All programs will be available in Districts 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 16, 19, 23, 27, 31, and 32. For more information about 3-K programs, please see the 2019-20 3-K Program List.

To find out what school district you live in, call 311.

To see 3-K for All programs, click Go to 3-K Finder Map below.

If you haven't found a Pre-K for All seat for this school year yet, it’s not too late! Click the Request a Call button below to have an Enrollment Specialist contact you to explore what options may be available.

Note: If your child was born in 2015, they are eligible for pre-K for the 2019-20 school year! If your child was born in 2016, they are eligible for 3-K programs for the 2019-20 school year in Districts 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 16, 19, 23, 27, 31, and 32.
